--------------------LAYOUT-----------------------
- one store for our demonstration, our store.
- a store has many transactions
- a store has many customers through transactions
- a customer has a name and can have many transactions

- a store has one inventory, an inventory can have many items
- the items will have a type column eg: bacon, eggs, cheese", and a quantity column.
- the store's inventory will be responsible for updating the quantity of it's items

- transactions will have a born-on date(time of purchase), customer_id and store_id
- transactions can have many orders 

- orders will belong to a transaction and have many item_quantities
- an item_quantities joins table will be created via a find query based through Inventory based on item "type"
- item_quantities will have an item_id and order_id and a quantity column, responsible for updating the items' inventory
------------------------------------------------------
